TASK_SCHEMA_VERSION=3
TASK_ID=304
TASK_TITLE=Live ASCII team grid on TUI Dashboard — real-time team visualization
TASK_STATUS=done
TASK_TYPE=feature
TASK_DESCRIPTION=Bring the ASCII art team grid from the startup loading screen to the Go TUI Dashboard as a permanent live widget. Instead of static art, it should show actual teams in real-time: which teams exist, their window/pane layout, worker status (BUSY/READY/FINISHED/RESERVED), and role labels. Think of it as a visual map of the tmux session — the user can see at a glance who's working, who's idle, and the overall grid shape. Research the current startup ASCII art (tui/cmd/doey-loading/ or shell startup code), then design a live version that polls team/pane status and renders on the Dashboard tab. Should look beautiful with Charmbracelet styling — box-drawing, colors per status, role icons.
TASK_SUBTASKS=1:W5.1: Research ASCII art loading screen code and team/pane data sources:done\n2:W5.2: Research Go TUI Dashboard architecture — widget system, data flow, rendering:done\n3:Dispatched to team 5 (2 workers):done\n4:W5.1: Implement renderTeamGrid() in dashboard.go — live team grid widget:done\n5:W5.2: Verify — build, review correctness, test rendering:done
